                    <Footer/>
                    <WebAddress>http://www.lsc.gov/grants-grantee-resources/our-grant-programs</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Grant Programs</Header>
                <Paragraph>Descriptions of the LSC's seven grant programs—basic field, disaster relief emergency, technology initiative, and veterans appeals pro bono grants; leadership development and loan repayment assistance programs; and pro bono innovation fund—are available online.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
            <EntitySourceOfInformation EntitySourceOfInformationId="2539" SortOrder="18">
                <FooterDetails>
                    <Email/>
                    <Footer/>
                    <WebAddress>http://www.lsc.gov/what-legal-aid/unmet-need-legal-aid</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Justice Gap</Header>
                <Paragraph>The justice gap represents the difference between the level of civil legal assistance that is available and the level that is necessary to meet the legal needs of low-income individuals and families. To learn more about the justice gap, visit the "The Unmet Need for Legal Aid" web page.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
